                                    Humboldt, ‚is for all the inhabitants of the torrid zone what
                                    the cereal gramina, wheat, barley, and rye, are for the western
                                    Asia, and for Europe […]. In the two continents […] the fruit of
                                    the banana is one of the most interesting objects of cultivation
                                    for the subsistence of man.‘ This observation is extremely
